      "content": "thanks for the tips. i noticed you mentioned that more \"traditional\" or \"established\" neighborhoods tend to be the more stable ones. is there a general rule of thumb for that? like, is it usually the case that more diverse or urban-feeling areas are the ones we should be cautious about if we want to avoid those social issues and instability? just trying to understand the pattern so we can make an informed decision.",
